 diffuse H$_2$ component or an abundance of CO-faint low column\ndensity molecular clouds. The H$_2$ content of evolved starburst rings may\ntherefore be substantially larger. Due to its lower $\\Sigma_{\\rm SFR}$ and age\nthe Cartwheel's inner ring has yet to reach this state. Alternately, the outer\nring may trigger efficient SF in an HI-dominated ISM.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Nov 2015 14:05:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-02"}
